laboratory_examinations.findings: Gallbladder is distended with wall thickening, mural edema, and surrounding fat stranding. Hyperemic appearance of the adjacent liver compatible with acute cholecystitis. No evidence of focal lesions or biliary dilatation. Common bile duct measures 5 mm.
No polymorphonuclear leukocytes seen. No microorganisms seen. Result: 3.5 mg/dL (reference range: 2.7 - 4.5 mg/dL).
